        <updateDate>2022-07-02T16:21:11Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Informing Grandfamilies Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires states to notify kinship caregivers (e.g., grandparents or other relatives caring for a minor child) about (1) the care and placement options under federal, state, and local laws; (2) the requirements to become a foster family home; (3) whether the state has elected to make guardianship assistance payments; and (4) other policies under the state program that may assist such caregivers.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
